				<td colspan="2"><span>Starssong, please don't let four or five members of this very large community make you think the other two or three hundred are that way.  What seems painfully obvious to some is obviously not so to others.  No one has the right to discount your skill or ability simply because you happened upon a circumstance you hadn't seen before far later in your bard levels than they did.  EACH ONE of the people who ridiculed you once had a moment where they, too, discovered to their chagrin that they couldn't equip a two instruments at once.  In my case, having started playing in 2000 before there were ANY primary/secondary instruments and only a tiny handful of primary only ones, I just assumed that a primary only lute (like the one in Veeshan's Peak) could be dual wielded with my Nostrolo's Tambourine.  Until I was told otherwise.  And I probably didn't find that out until level 50 or later.  It is a piece of information that could easily have eluded me for 10 more levels if I hadn't stumbled across the possibility.
