				<td colspan="2"><span>Reys - all I ask is that folks realize that not everyone playing these games are young and accustomed to all the ins and outs of RPGs - and that they have great memories.  I am (horrors) 48 years old - and, as I said, my main computer game experience before this was Tetris.  I may have encountered this issue before.  I honestly don't remember.  My nephew, who got me hooked on this game, teases me mercilessly about the things I just don't retain.  Who knows, maybe I have early Altzheimers.  
<br />

<br />
I think there is a generation of &quot;gamers&quot; that make the assumption that anyone who plays as long and as much as I have is going to have all this stuff down to a &quot;T&quot;.  I, apparently, don't have the right &quot;personality&quot; or mental agility (though I am not saying I am stupid).  I think there are &quot;right brain&quot; &quot;left brain&quot; issues at play - who knows.  I also know I am not a very good &quot;multi-tasker&quot;, so I get distracted easily, and things I have learned, will sometimes seem to just leak right out of my brain! lol
<br />

<br />
I guess, all I am asking, is that folks take the time to realize that not all of us in this game - even us that are elemental, have KT access (not Time flagged yet - still need Coirnav and TRC) are completely capable in ALL areas of the game or our class.  I rely HEAVILY on my guildies and on other bards in the game.  Sometimes, I may ask a question more than once.  Maybe I didn't pay close attention the first time I got it answered.  Or, maybe, it just leaked out of my brain.  
<br />

<br />
Just give some of us old folks - or just leaky brained folks in general - the benefit of the doubt.  And, &quot;do unto others&quot; as you would like to be done unto! lol
<br />

<br />
I would never &quot;mock&quot; you for any issue you were dealing with.  I just ask the same respect.  
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the hand you've offered Steppy.  Reys - I hope you are able to come down off your &quot;high horse&quot; and realize that not all of us out here are &quot;computer nerds&quot; and &quot;uber gamers&quot;.  Some of us are just normal folks having a lot of fun and making friends and experiencing challenges in a wonderfully complex game called Everquest.  The next time someone asks you for a bit of advice, I hope you'll reach out your hand and help them out - without beating them about the head and shoulders and telling them they should already know the answer.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
