				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm going to keep defending Starssong's experience here.  I think it is not the least bit unbelievable that it took that long to finally have an instrument with both PRI/SEC capability -- face it, not everyone has access to them and if you are a casual player, you can get to 65 in 4 years without bazaar twinking or becoming an uber soloist -- I know I did.  And in that situation, you can suddenly find youself having access to gear you never saw before in 3+ years and lets face it -- the way Sony has those labelled IMPLIES that you can dual wield them and it's not like there are 2 dozen discussion threads on this board covering the topic.  I honestly feel the folks who blindly ASSUMED Starssong was e-bayed should be ashamed of themselves.  It's unusual to play this long without discovering this fact.  To assume it is not possible to have done so is clearly shortsighted.
<br />

<br />
Starssong, I'm 46.  Unlike you, I have a long and geeky history in this business as a tech writer and analyst with a major computer company to go with a few years of computer gaming.  Message boards (and to a lesser extent e-mail) invite people to express themselves without accountability and as a result, folks lash out in a way that real-life proximity and manners would normally prohibit.  You're old enough to know there is a HUGE difference between the face some of these folks throw on here in these forums and what they must be like in real life.  Consider the names and faces here to be costumes and roles being played by people not that different from yourself and you can laugh off a lot of the crap.
<br />

<br />
Except for me, of course.  I am totally sincere and honest 100% of the time here.  Ask anyone!  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" /></span></td>
